issue.title: `FastifySecureSession` type is not compatible with `FastifyPluginCallback`
issue.body:
### Prerequisites

- [x] I have written a descriptive issue title
- [x] I have searched existing issues to ensure the bug has not already been reported


### Fastify version

5.5.0

### Plugin version

8.2.0

### Node.js version

24.0

### Operating system

macOS

### Operating system version (i.e. 20.04, 11.3, 10)

15.6

### Description

When using the `fastifySecureSession` callback as a plugin for my nestjs fastify project, I get a typescript error:

```
Argument of type 'FastifySecureSession' is not assignable to parameter of type 'FastifyPluginCallback<SecureSessionPluginOptions | (SecureSessionPluginOptions & Required<Pick<SecureSessionPluginOptions, "sessionName">>)[]> | FastifyPluginAsync<...> | Promise<...> | Promise<...>'.
  Type 'FastifySecureSession' is not assignable to type 'FastifyPluginCallback<SecureSessionPluginOptions | (SecureSessionPluginOptions & Required<Pick<SecureSessionPluginOptions, "sessionName">>)[]>'.
    Types of parameters 'instance' and 'instance' are incompatible.
```

This is my `main.ts` file:
```ts
import { fastifySecureSession } from "@fastify/secure-session";
...
  await app.register(fastifySecureSession, {
    expiry: configService.get("session.expiry"),
    cookieName: configService.get("session.cookieName"),
    secret: configService.get("session.secret"),
    salt: configService.get("session.salt"),
    cookie: {
      path: "/",
      secure: true,
      sameSite: "none",
      expires: new Date(Date.now() + configService.get("session.expiry") * 1000),
    },
  });
...
```
I belief there is a mismatch between the fastify version 5.5 and this plugin.

Thanks for your support.

### Link to code that reproduces the bug

-

### Expected Behavior

_No response_

comment.body:
> I belief there is a mismatch between the fastify version 5.5 and this plugin.

That is indeed the case. The problem is because the type for `fastifySecureSession` are based on the fastify dependency, which is a `devDependency`, so the version 5.0.0 is used. The types for version 5.0.0 are not compatible with 5.5.0.

Maybe a solution would be to reference fastify as a `peerDependency` and not being too strict with the version.

**suggestion (code-quality):** Inline variable that is immediately returned ([`inline-immediately-returned-variable`](https://docs.sourcery.ai/Reference/Rules-and-In-Line-Suggestions/TypeScript/Default-Rules/inline-immediately-returned-variable)) ```suggestion return Array.from({ length: n }).reduce( (current, _) => current?.parentElement, element ); ```
ExplanationSomething that we often see in people's code is assigning to a result variable and then immediately returning it. Returning the result directly shortens the code and removes an unnecessary variable, reducing the mental load of reading the function. Where intermediate variables can be useful is if they then get used as a parameter or a condition, and the name can act like a comment on what the variable represents. In the case where you're returning it from a function, the function name is there to tell you what the result is, so the variable name is unnecessary.

Delivers TASK-489 by improving URL detection, capture flow, and UI reliability. - New Features - Generic social parsing types (ISocialPost, IWebpageParser) and a shared save flow in the clipper store. - New SocialClipButton and SocialProfileClipButton used across sites; removed Twitter-only script. - Expanded URL detection and content types for all supported networks; added Reddit post/sub support. - Screenshot-only pages updated (e.g., X home, LinkedIn feed, Bluesky home) to avoid noisy captures. - Refactors - Node types expanded for new social posts/profiles; content preview handles Bluesky/Threads. - Capture type tweaks (omit parent during capture) and renamed Reddit thread to post. - UI/UX hardening: default toolbar side set, force extension visibility to avoid site overrides (e.g., Reddit), updated feedback messages. - Icons bundle updated and help modal links/version refreshed. **PR Summary by Typo** ------------ **Overview:** This PR introduces support for clipping social media posts and profiles from various platforms, including Twitter, LinkedIn, Bluesky, Threads, Instagram, Facebook, Mastodon, and Reddit. It adds new types, utilities, and components for parsing and saving social media data. It also removes the `TwitterContentScript.svelte` file and introduces a more generalized `SocialClipButton.svelte` component. **Key Changes:** - Adds new types for social media posts and profiles in `clipper.type.ts` and `node.type.ts`. - Implements parsing logic for various social media platforms in `clipper.utils.ts`. - Introduces `SocialClipButton.svelte` and `SocialProfileClipButton.svelte` for clipping social media content. - Updates `ContentScript.svelte` to use the new social clipping components and logic. - Modifies `resource.type.ts` to include a "parent" field for social media posts. - Updates `urlMap.ts` to include additional social media platforms for screenshot-only clipping. - Updates various other files for minor fixes and improvements. **Recommendations:** Not deployment ready. Improve error handling in the parsing logic to gracefully handle unexpected data formats and provide more informative error messages to the user. ### üóÇÔ∏è Work Breakdown | Category | Lines Changed | |-------------|---------------| | New Work | 2877 (88.6%) | | Churn | 205 (6.3%) | | Rework | 165 (5.1%) | | Total Changes | 3247 |
